This App is a great tool for using Wikipedia. It has customization features and browser integration, both of which makes exploring Wikipedia much easier. As much as I like it, however, there are some flaws. For example, when editing an article I'm unable to ticket "minor edit". I understand the rationale for why this might be the case, but it may be useful to add the feature for autoconfirmed contributors.  There is also limited integration of the talk pages or userpages on Wikipedia, and you can only access them manually if you know the landing page. Unfortunately, even after you get there it's all poorly optimized and unable to load properly. I understand why this is the case, but perhaps Wikipedia could improve this part of its App so as to allow editors greater access to behind the scenes while on the go. This is not essential, but it would definitely be helpful.  I previously commented about a lack of a any way to share the article links. I was wrong and I'm glad that the developers corrected me on that. It's a bit out of the way, so I honestly am not surprised that I didn't find it, but I'm fine with how it works (though adding it to the drop-down menu wouldn't hurt).
